article.headline: Navy 82, Lafayette 80
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Clif Colbert hit a jumper with two seconds remaining to give Navy an 82-80 win over Lafayette on Saturday. Matt Betley's 3-pointer tied it for Lafayette (14-11) with 34 seconds to go before Navy (13-12) drove down the court for Colbert's winning shot. Betley then turned the ball over with a second left to seal the win for Navy. Greg Sprink led Navy with a game-high 24 points and 11 rebounds, while Chris Harris scored 22 and Colbert added 18. Betley led Lafayette with 15 points and six rebounds. Andrew Brown and Bilal Abdullah each added 14 in the loss. The game was tied at 46 at the half and remained tight throughout the second half. There were 10 lead changes and seven ties overall.
